  <title>Scotland Malawi Partnership : David Livingstone Bicentenary Scholarships</title>
  <description>The Scholarship Programme will give 30-50 young, gifted, under-privileged Malawian students the opportunity to study at a Malawian further or higher education institute. The programme will operate to ensure that at least 50% of scholars are female and will ensure diversity among the candidates. Candidates will be required to illustrate how their scholarship will benefit not only them as individuals, but also their wider communities. The selection of Malawian institutes for inclusion in this programme will take account of existing links with Scottish institutions and the types of courses supported will be within the thematic areas relevant to the Malawian Government&apos;s Growth and development Strategy and its National Education Sector Programme.</description>
